<TITLE> Bangla, Religious Studies pre-tests on Aug 4, 10 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 9 (bdnews24.com)The Bangla Paper I (compulsory) and Religious Studies pre-tests for the students scheduled to take the SSC examinations in 2010 will be held on Aug 4 and 10, the an education ministry has said in a circular, issued Wednesday said. The pre-tests will be held in the creative questions system simultaneously across the country in a manner similar to the SSC examinations and controlled centrally, the circular issued on Wednesday said. Similar method and operational modes will be applied while holding the tests subsequently, the ministry added, that is, the tests again will be held on the same days all over as announced using the same test papers. Bangladesh Examination Development Unit will be responsible for centrally organising the pre-test and test papers setting, printing and supplying to the education boards. b
